<TEXT>
A fleet of electric cars may be launched in Coventry in 1996. Warwickshire
Institute is conducting a Pounds 50,000 feasibility study on the scheme for
the city and Peugeot, the French car company.
The project, backed by a consortium which includes PowerGen, IBM and East
Midlands Electricity, is planned to coincide with the centenary of the
British car industry and a redevelopment of the city centre. It is likely to
provide electric cars hired for individual journeys using a 'smart card'
electronic monitoring system.
