FT  24 FEB 94 / Customs initiated third of failures
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Customs and Excise were responsible for more than a third of all company
winding-up orders in England and Wales in the last financial year - up from
just over 17 per cent in 1987-88.
Mr Neil Hamilton, trade and industry minister, said in a written answer that
3,434 company winding-up orders had been made following petitions by Customs
and Excise. This was out of a total of 9,542 orders. In 1987-88 just 690 of
the 3,952 winding-up orders were made following Customs and Excise
petitions.
