FT  23 FEB 94 / International Company News: US media groups in TV shopping
deal for Japan
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD TOMKINS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Home Shopping Network and Tele-Communications of the US yesterday announced
they had set up a joint venture with Sumitomo of Japan to introduce a
television shopping channel in Japan. Transmissions are expected to begin
within a year.
The three companies have signed a letter of intent as a first step towards
establishing a television shopping business in Japan similar to those
already operating in the US. They said they hoped to involve other big
companies in the venture.
Home Shopping Network at present operates three cable and broadcast services
capable of reaching 60m viewers in the US. It said recently-announced
changes in Japanese government policy on television regulation had opened
the way to greater openness in cable and direct-to-home distribution.
The companies said the channel would be tested soon after a feasibility
study.
