FT  23 FEB 94 / UK Company News: Buckingham confirms Pounds 10m sale
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
As part of its support plan Buckingham International, the hotels and leisure
group, has confirmed the previously announced sale of one of its Portuguese
subsidiaries, Morlaix de Portugal Investimentos Hoteleiros e Turisticos,
which owns the Holiday Inn hotel in Lisbon.
The Es2.5bn (Pounds 9.7m) sale and other asset disposals are part of the
plan Buckingham has agreed with its bankers to give a period of stability in
which to reduce borrowings by October 31 1994.
Part of that plan involves loan stock holders sanctioning the payment of the
cash proceeds of the Holiday Inn to the group's bankers, in exchange for
first ranking security over a similar asset, the Holiday Inn Crowne Plaza,
Lisbon.
