<HEADLINE>
FT  23 FEB 94 / Observer: Time and Tigue
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A change of chief investment officer at Foreign &amp; Colonial Management, one
of the City's most successful fund managers, still gives no clue about the
bigger question of who's going to succeed investment veteran Michael Hart,
chairman of F&amp;C's management company. Hart turns 62 in December, so could
have two or three more years in the saddle. But one name is already
beginning to emerge as his likely successor to run the fast-expanding group
and that is Jeremy Tigue, who joined in 1981. At just 34, Tigue need not be
impatient.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Foreign and Colonial Management.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
