FT  23 FEB 94 / Observer: Leaderless in . . .
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
And just what is wrong with Leeds anyway? One year to the day since Mike
Blackburn said he was quitting as boss of Leeds Permanent building society
to head for Halifax, the UK's fifth-biggest society still lacks a chief
executive.
Even allowing for an interruption while the society flirted with National &amp;
Provincial, it's clear that qualified candidates have scarcely been falling
over themselves to apply. Leeds insists it doesn't feel snubbed and
underlines how well it's doing under its existing management. So why does
its spokesman have to say 'if you're writing something, say that Leeds is a
nice place; it's a very vibrant northern city'?
