FT  23 FEB 94 / Observer: Two-faced
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Meanwhile, The Royal Bank of Scotland is giving a whole new meaning to joint
accounts. The bank, which pioneered the use of photos on credit cards, says
it would be quite happy to issue two cards to transvestites  - one featuring
a photograph of them as a man and one as a woman.
According to Janet Scott, president of the Beaumont Society, which runs
helplines for transvestites, having two photo cards could prove very
convenient for some cross-dressers. 'Those who are confident enough to go
shopping in their female persona would certainly want to have a second
card.'
And you could still blame the shopping spree on your other half.
</TEXT>
