<HEADLINE>
FT  23 FEB 94 / Leaked drug report sparks row
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The government's policy on drug misuse was under attack yesterday after
leaked papers showed it had altered a report calling for a coherent approach
to the problem.
Two versions of a report by the Department of Health show the original paper
containing criticism of the government's failure to provide a co-ordinated
drugs policy. In the final version the title has been changed, important
passages calling for a new partnership to tackle the problem in local
communities have been watered down and some chapters omitted.
Mr Tony Blair, shadow home secretary, said: 'These two versions are
drastically different with every sign that hard-hitting recommendations have
been deliberately watered down.'
</TEXT>
