FT  23 FEB 94 / Education quango selection attacked
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN AUTHERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Labour last night alleged that the government had 'put political dogma
before education' in selecting members for the new quango which will control
funding for grant-maintained schools in England and Wales, John Authers
writes.
The only representative of a local authority on the Funding Agency for
Schools, which will have powers to plan education provision alongside
education authorities, is Mr Edward Lister, leader of the Conservative
'flagship' borough of Wandsworth.
Members also include two directors of the Thatcherite Centre for Policy
Studies - Mr Stanley Kalms, chairman of Dixons, and Sir Robert Balchin of
the Grant-maintained Schools Foundation - as well as three heads and one
governor of grant-maintained schools.
