<HEADLINE>
FT  23 FEB 94 / Israel tots up cost of settlers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID HOROVITZ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JERUSALEM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
While publicly insisting it has no plans to dismantle Jewish settlements in
the occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip, the Israeli government has begun
calculating the cost of rehousing the estimated 32,000 Jewish settler
families in homes inside Israel's sovereign borders, a report on state
television said last night.
The report claimed the Finance Ministry has drawn up a working paper which
estimates the cost of rehousing the settlers at Dollars 300,000 per family,
implying a total Dollars 9.6bn (Pounds 6.5bn) to move the entire settler
population.
Under its framework agreement with the Palestinian Liberation Organisation
on limited self-rule for the Palestinians of the occupied territories,
Israel is not obliged to dismantle any of the 140-plus Jewish settlements
over the next five years. The settlements' final status has been left for
negotiation at talks scheduled to begin in 1996.
