FT  23 FEB 94 / Leak shuts down Russian N-plant
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Reuter
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MNOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
One of four units at the Sosnovy Bor nuclear plant near Russia's second
city, St Petersburg, was shut down yesterday after a 'small leakage of
water', Interfax news agency said, Reuter reports from Moscow.
A routine check revealed a hole in a welded section of pipe in the reactor's
emergency cooling system, the report said. A leak at Sosnovy Bor in March
1992 triggered international concern, with radioactive iodine and inert
gases escaping after a loss of pressure in a reactor channel.
The Norwegian radiation protection authority said of the incident: 'The
reactor is now in a stable, shut-down condition with normal cooling. There
has been no emission exceeding the permitted limits.'
